nd track can be dragged, if the track is dragged and thrown the velocity of the throw is added to the tracks velocity and it slows gradually to a stop.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"If the thumb is currently being dragged and reachs the minimum or maximum value of its bounds, velocity is added to the track in the opposite direction of the drag.","type":"text"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"OverflowSlider","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/Sliders\/documentation\/Sliders\/OverflowSlider","role":"symbol"},"doc://Sliders/documentation/Sliders":{"role":"collection","title":"Sliders","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A collection of fully stylable, drag-based SwiftUI controls — including linear, radial, range, and 2D sliders."}],"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/sliders","identifier":"doc:\/\/Sliders\/documentation\/Sliders","kind":"symbol"}}}